{
  "texts": [
    "First, as many occupied bands as possible are grouped into spinpolarized versions of the spinless KIVC bands described above.",
    "This maximizes the exchange gain due to λ and superexchange due to J.",
    "For even ν, the construction ends here, yielding a maximally intervalley-coherent state with C = 0.",
    "For odd ν, the leftover occupied band is chosen to be valley-polarized, leading to a total |C| = 1 [35].",
    "1 summarizes the result at each filling assuming spin-collinear density matrices (though recall that the residual SU (2) K × SU (2) K ′ flavor symmetry can be used to generate degenerate solutions).|ν| State Spin pol."
  ]
}